<h1>Problem 2280 - 2025 China Mathematical Olympiad, P5 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(p\) be a prime number and \(f\) be a bijection from \(\left\{0,1,\ldots,p-1\right\}\) to itself. Suppose that for integers \(a,b \in \left\{0,1,\ldots,p-1\right\}\), \(|f(a) - f(b)|\leqslant 2024\) if \(p \mid a^2 - b\). Prove that there exists infinite many \(p\) such that there exists such an \(f\) and there also exists infinite many \(p\) such that there doesn&#x27;t exist such an \(f\).</p>
